Incident: LS Command Detected in Requested URL

Indicators:
  Alert Trigger Reason : URL Contains LS 
  Source IP: 172.16.17.46
  Source port: 46843
  Destination IP: 188.114.96.15
  Destination Port: 443
  Protocol: HTTPS

Investigation:
Understanding why alert was triggered:
  URL Contains LS

Traffic information:
SOURCE:
  After researching ip address the IP address is actually owned by an endpoint in the company. 

DESTINATION:
  After researching the ip address, when searching the endpoints on the SIEM, the same system from the source domain pops up. And putting it into ARIN Whois/RDAP we see it's a cloud flare server.

PROTOCOL
  The protocol being used: HTTPS

Findings:
  After analyzing the request: https://letsdefend.io/blog/?s=skills, we see this isnt an LS command, and a false positive was triggered. This was a user on the company network searching for something on a server webpage, nothing else.

Just to make sure we analyze the other traffic from this domain, and nothing is malicous. 
Conclusion:
False positive.

Response:
No escalation required.
